How are ratings calculated?

Mike PowersTop Contributor: Chess
TOP 1000 REVIEWER
5.0 out of 5 stars Trevor Pinnock and the English Concert deliver terrific performances of Bach's Brandenburg Concertos and Orchestral Suites..
Reviewed in the United States on July 12, 2017
Verified Purchase
I just couldn’t help myself. I tried very hard to refrain from purchasing another set of Johann Sebastian Bach’s Brandenburg Concertos and Orchestral Suites. But, after listening to the MP3 album of Trevor Pinnock and the English Concert’s rendition of these Bach masterworks, and after reading the overwhelmingly positive reviews of this album, I couldn’t stop myself. I bought the 3-compact disc (CD) set (and, as a bonus, got a free MP3 download of it as well.)

Trevor Pinnock and The English Concert, a period-instrument orchestra that Pinnock helped found in the mid-1970s, exhibit a joyful enthusiasm and an obvious love of the music they are playing. This is readily evident in every note they play. Tempi are quick but not too hurried in the Allegro and Presto movements of both the Brandenburg Concertos and the Orchestral Suites, and the Adagio and Andante movements are always properly deliberate and measured without ever becoming lethargic. Trevor Pinnock’s wonderfully sizzling harpsichord solo in Brandenburg Concerto No. 5 is breathtaking, and must be heard to be believed.

When I began listening to this album for the first time on my 30-year old CD player with its 5-disc changer, and my 5.1-channel home theater system, I was amazed by the superb audio quality. Each Brandenburg Concerto and Orchestral Suite possesses a wonderfully clear, warm, and well-balanced sound. I could easily hear every plucked string of Pinnock’s harpsichord, every drawn bow over violins, violas da gamba, and cellos, and every note sounded from horns and woodwinds. Pinnock and his band maintain just the right period-instrument pungency that makes this “historically informed performance” a sheer delight from beginning to end.

I’m very glad that I was unable to resist the temptation to add just one more album of Johann Sebastian Bach’s Brandenburg Concertos and Orchestral Suites to my music library. This terrific 3-CD set by Trevor Pinnock and The English Concert is now my clear favorite among all my classical music recordings. Most highly recommended.

I owned both collections separately as LP's, many years ago, of course, so it is a delight to have them again in this format.
